The vain conceits of the presumptuous Wights
I but abhor the Slavery of Man
No more such Wild Fantastic things
My Breast ; nor these Serener Thoughts Alarm
the Offencive , Hated Face of Man
of my fate Thou'st lost a Politician in thy State
Thou'st lost a Politician in thy State
lost a Politician in thy State
To fool the World with more delusive Charms
its way to the Great 's heart :
A proud contemner of thy Laws
A proud contemner of thy Laws
no more my freedom to surprise , Which nothing can control but Theron's eyes
all the Air of that Bewitching Face , My Pride and Resolutions
Of the false Charmer meanly to complain
urge my Breast with a more active fire
more of Hymen , or of Love
